The Nautilus DevOps team needs a time check pod created in a specific Kubernetes namespace for logging purposes. Initially, it's for testing, but it may be integrated into an existing cluster later. Here's what's required:


Create a pod called time-check in the datacenter namespace. The pod should contain a container named time-check, utilizing the busybox image with the latest tag (specify as busybox:latest).

Create a config map named time-config with the data TIME_FREQ=4 in the same namespace.

Configure the time-check container to execute the command: while true; do date; sleep $TIME_FREQ;done. Ensure the result is written /opt/sysops/time/time-check.log. Also, add an environmental variable TIME_FREQ in the container, fetching its value from the config map TIME_FREQ key.

Create a volume log-volume and mount it at /opt/sysops/time within the container.

Note: The kubectl utility on the jump-host has been configured to work with the Kubernetes cluster.



-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
thor@jump-host ~$ k create namespace datacenter
namespace/datacenter created

thor@jump-host ~$ kubectl config set-context --current  --namespace=datacenter
Context "default" modified.

thor@jump-host ~$ kubectl create configmap time-config --from-literal=TIME_FREQ=4
configmap/time-config created


thor@jump-host ~$ cat time-check.yaml 
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: time-check
spec:
  containers:
    - name: time-check
      image: busybox:latest
      command: ["/bin/sh", "-c"]
      args:
        [
          "while true; do date; sleep $TIME_FREQ; done> /opt/sysops/time/time-check.log"
        ]
      volumeMounts:
        - mountPath: /opt/sysops/time
          name: log-volume
      env:
        - name: TIME_FREQ 
          valueFrom:
            configMapKeyRef:
              name: time-config
              key: TIME_FREQ
  volumes:
    - name: log-volume
      emptyDir: {}

  restartPolicy: Never


thor@jump-host ~$ k apply -f time-check.yaml 
pod/time-check created

